.TH "vmw_validation_add_resource" 9 "vmw_validation_add_resource" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_validation_add_resource \- Add a resource to the validation context.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_validation_add_resource
.BI "(struct vmw_validation_context *ctx "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_resource *res "  ","
.BI "size_t priv_size "  ","
.BI "u32 dirty "  ","
.BI "void **p_node "  ","
.BI "bool *first_usage "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
The validation context.
.IP "res" 12
The resource.
.IP "priv_size" 12
Size of private, additional metadata.
.IP "dirty" 12
Whether to change dirty status.
.IP "p_node" 12
Output pointer of additional metadata address.
.IP "first_usage" 12
Whether this was the first time this resource was seen.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative error code otherwise.
